  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Capacities of the Government of Bosnia And Herzegovina to Provide Protection Sensitive Services within the Migration Response in Lipa, Una Sana Canton</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project to support the new Temporary Reception Centre (TRC) Lipa, which will accommodate up to 1,500 migrants, and be managed directly by the Ministry of Security (MoS) of Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH), through the Service for Foreigner Affairs (SFA). This intervention will ensure access to systematic and protection-sensitive reception and accommodation services in TRC Lipa, specifically covering the costs of field assistants providing front-line assistance to migrants in transit, as well as social workers assisting vulnerable migrants, and team leaders providing camp coordination and management support.</narrative>
  </description>
